      "description": "Charisma Saving Throw: DC [[lookup @save.dc.value activity=7gmNBVjwuYTyANMe]], one [[lookup @target.affects.special activity=7gmNBVjwuYTyANMe]] the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} can see within [[lookup @range.value activity=7gmNBVjwuYTyANMe]] feet.\n\nFailure: The target is possessed by the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster}; the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} disappears, and the target has the &amp;Reference[Incapacitated apply=false] condition and loses control of its body. The [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} now controls the body, but the target retains awareness. The [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} can't be targeted by any attack, spell, or other effect, except ones that specifically target Undead. The [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster}'s game statistics are the same, except it uses the possessed target's Speed, as well as the target's Strength, Dexterity, and Constitution modifiers.\n\nThe possession lasts until the body drops to 0 Hit Points or the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} leaves as a Bonus Action. When the possession ends, the [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster} appears in an unoccupied space within 5 feet of the target, and the target is immune to this ghost's Possession for 24 hours.\n\nSuccess: The target is immune to this [[lookup @name lowercase]]{monster}'s Possession for 24 hours.",
